---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Care Instructions - Kanix™"
  description="Care and maintenance instructions for Kanix™ 3D-printed dog handler belt modules, organized by material type."
>
  <nav class="fixed top-0 w-full z-50 bg-neutral-950/80 backdrop-blur-md border-b border-neutral-800">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL} class="text-xl font-extrabold tracking-tight hover:text-neutral-300 transition-colors">KANIX<sup class="text-[0.5em] align-super">™</sup></a>
      <div class="hidden sm:flex items-center gap-6">
        <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL} class="text-sm text-neutral-400 hover:text-white transition-colors">Home</a>
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}products/`} class="text-sm text-neutral-400 hover:text-white transition-colors">Shop</a>
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}kits/`} class="text-sm text-neutral-400 hover:text-white transition-colors">Kits</a>
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}checkout/`} class="text-sm text-neutral-400 hover:text-white transition-colors" id="cart-link">
          Cart <span id="cart-count" class="hidden ml-1 px-1.5 py-0.5 bg-amber-500 text-neutral-950 text-xs font-bold rounded-full"></span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main id="main" class="pt-20 pb-16 px-4 sm:px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL} class="text-sm text-neutral-500 hover:text-white transition-colors mb-6 inline-block">
        &larr; Back to home
      </a>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">Care Instructions</h1>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        Proper care extends the life of your Kanix™ modules. Follow the guidelines below for your specific material type.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-12">
        <!-- General Care -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">General Care (All Materials)</h2>
          <ul class="text-neutral-400 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
            <li>Inspect modules regularly for cracks, warping, or layer separation</li>
            <li>Replace any part showing signs of structural compromise</li>
            <li>Clean with mild soap and lukewarm water — avoid harsh chemicals or solvents</li>
            <li>Dry thoroughly before reattaching to belt hardware</li>
            <li>Check bolt tightness periodically — vibration during use can loosen hardware</li>
            <li>Store in a cool, dry place away from direct sunlight when not in use</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- Material-Specific Care -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-6">Material-Specific Care</h2>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <!-- TPU -->
            <div class="bg-amber-500/5 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-xl p-6">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                <span class="px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider bg-amber-500/10 text-amber-500 rounded-full border border-amber-500/20">Flexible</span>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">TPU (Thermoplastic Polyurethane)</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-1"><strong class="text-white">Max temperature:</strong> 60°C (140°F)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                TPU is your most flexible and impact-resistant option. It absorbs shock well and resists cracking, making it ideal for modules that may experience drops or rough handling.
              </p>
              <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-300 mb-2">Care Tips</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-neutral-400 space-y-1.5 list-disc pl-5">
                <li><strong class="text-white">Never leave in a hot car</strong> — interior temperatures can exceed 60°C in summer, causing permanent deformation</li>
                <li>TPU is resistant to many oils and greases, but avoid prolonged contact with acetone or strong solvents</li>
                <li>Flexibility means TPU parts may stretch slightly over time under constant load — this is normal</li>
                <li>Clean with warm water and mild soap; TPU handles moisture well</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- TPC -->
            <div class="bg-amber-500/5 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-xl p-6">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                <span class="px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider bg-green-500/10 text-green-500 rounded-full border border-green-500/20">Premium</span>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">TPC (Thermoplastic Copolyester)</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-1"><strong class="text-white">Max temperature:</strong> 130°C (266°F)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                TPC is the most durable and heat-resistant material in the Kanix™ lineup. It offers excellent chemical resistance and maintains its shape under demanding conditions.
              </p>
              <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-300 mb-2">Care Tips</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-neutral-400 space-y-1.5 list-disc pl-5">
                <li>Safe to leave in vehicles — TPC can withstand typical car interior temperatures</li>
                <li>Resistant to most chemicals including oils, fuels, and cleaning agents</li>
                <li>While highly durable, TPC can still crack under extreme point impacts — avoid dropping on hard surfaces from height</li>
                <li>No special storage requirements beyond general care guidelines</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- PLA -->
            <div class="bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-xl p-6">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                <span class="px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-400 rounded-full border border-neutral-700">Basic</span>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">PLA (Polylactic Acid)</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-1"><strong class="text-white">Max temperature:</strong> 50°C (122°F)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                PLA is rigid and produces excellent surface finish but has the lowest heat tolerance. Best suited for indoor use or moderate climates.
              </p>
              <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-300 mb-2">Care Tips</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-neutral-400 space-y-1.5 list-disc pl-5">
                <li><strong class="text-white">Never leave in a hot car or in direct sunlight</strong> — PLA can warp at temperatures as low as 50°C</li>
                <li>PLA is more brittle than TPU or PETG — avoid impacts and sudden flexing</li>
                <li>PLA is biodegradable and may degrade with prolonged moisture exposure — dry after cleaning</li>
                <li>Not recommended for use in hot or humid climates without frequent inspection</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- PETG -->
            <div class="bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-xl p-6">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                <span class="px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-400 rounded-full border border-neutral-700">Standard</span>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">PETG (Polyethylene Terephthalate Glycol)</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-1"><strong class="text-white">Max temperature:</strong> 80°C (176°F)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                PETG offers a strong balance of durability, heat resistance, and ease of printing. A versatile all-rounder suitable for most conditions.
              </p>
              <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-300 mb-2">Care Tips</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-neutral-400 space-y-1.5 list-disc pl-5">
                <li>Generally safe in vehicles during moderate temperatures, but avoid leaving on dashboards in peak summer</li>
                <li>Good moisture resistance — no special drying requirements</li>
                <li>More impact-resistant than PLA but less flexible than TPU</li>
                <li>Avoid strong solvents like acetone, which can cloud or weaken PETG</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- ABS -->
            <div class="bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-xl p-6">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                <span class="px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider bg-neutral-800 text-neutral-400 rounded-full border border-neutral-700">Standard</span>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">ABS (Acrylonitrile Butadiene Styrene)</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-1"><strong class="text-white">Max temperature:</strong> 100°C (212°F)</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                ABS is impact-resistant and heat-tolerant, making it suitable for parts that may experience rough handling or moderate heat exposure.
              </p>
              <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-300 mb-2">Care Tips</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-neutral-400 space-y-1.5 list-disc pl-5">
                <li>Good heat resistance — generally safe in vehicles</li>
                <li><strong class="text-white">Avoid acetone</strong> — ABS dissolves in acetone (this property is used intentionally for smoothing, but accidental exposure weakens parts)</li>
                <li>UV exposure can cause yellowing and brittleness over time — store out of direct sunlight</li>
                <li>Good impact resistance but can crack along layer lines under sustained stress</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- When to Replace -->
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">When to Replace</h2>
          <div class="text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>Replace any Kanix™ module immediately if you notice:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
              <li>Visible cracks or fractures, especially around bolt holes or stress points</li>
              <li>Warping or deformation that prevents proper seating on the belt</li>
              <li>Layer separation (delamination) visible as white lines or peeling layers</li>
              <li>Excessive wear that reduces grip, retention force, or structural integrity</li>
              <li>Bolt holes that have become enlarged or stripped</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Safety Disclaimer -->
        <section>
          <div class="bg-neutral-900 border border-neutral-800 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-neutral-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Safety Disclaimer</h2>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs leading-relaxed">
              3D-printed parts can vary in strength and durability depending on material, print settings, and environmental conditions. These products are designed as accessories for dog handling belts and are not safety-critical equipment. Inspect your modules regularly and replace any parts showing signs of wear, cracking, or deformation. Kanix™ is not responsible for injury, damage, or loss resulting from the use of these products. Always supervise dogs when using any handling equipment. Use at your own risk.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="py-12 px-6 border-t border-neutral-800">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto text-center text-sm text-neutral-500 space-y-2">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}warranty/`} class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Warranty</a>
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}returns/`} class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Returns</a>
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}care/`} class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Care Instructions</a>
      </div>
      <p>&copy; 2026 mmmaxwwwell. All rights reserved. Kanix™ designs are original works by mmmaxwwwell.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>
